GAFFTAhours: Powers of 10 – A 2010 NYE Membership Drive Celebration
Mark Zuckerberg was invited
Following the tradition of our memorable Grand Opening GAFFTAhours party, Powers of 10 will be a multimedia celebration featuring original works from world class audio and visual artists, including a LIVE performance from (and the San Francisco premiere of) internationally acclaimed DJ and producer Brendon Moeller! Preview Brendon's signature sound on this brand new mix compiled exclusively for the impeccable Modyfier blog: http://soundcloud.com/modyfier/brendon-moeller-process-part-179 Paying homage to the base 10 nature of the year ahead (and the inspirational scientific short film of the same name) Powers of 10 will transform our dynamic 4,000 sq ft. digital art center into a series of distinct audiovisual spaces and exhibitions exploring the microscopic and macrocosmic dimensions of our collective interconnectivity. And for this special occasion, we are excited to have 6 channels from The Compound’s legendary sound-system at our disposal to create a truly immersive environment. With local support from SF stalwarts Jonah Sharp, Alland Byallo and Nikola Baytala, OPEN BAR until midnight, champagne toast, hors d’œuvres, balloon drop, and a full fledged GAFFTA Membership, Powers of 10 promises to be a celebration worthy of the arrival of a new decade filled with promise and possibilities. Powers of 10 is a Members only (21+) event. You can reserve your spot by purchasing a GAFFTA Membership at any level (see below). Membership perks include discounts on future GAFFTA events, Members-only keepsakes and the first 75 Memberships sold come with a limited edition GAFFTA pin! (Existing Members are asked to RSVP, and will be contacted soon with more details.) All proceeds directly fund GAFFTA’s operating and production expenses, and memberships are 100% tax deductible. By becoming a GAFFTA Member you will be stakeholder in our shared vision of building social consciousness through digital culture…and what could make a better Holiday gift than a GAFFTA Membership and the hottest ticket in town?! Capacity is strictly limited and sales are online only, so become a Member, support GAFFTA and secure your spot at the party of the (next) decade now! Purchase your GAFFTA Membership here! http://www.gaffta.org/2009/12/08/gafftahours-powers-of-10-a-2010-new-years-eve-celebration/ $40 *Discount Holiday Gray Membership includes: 1 ticket to Powers of 10 1 year GAFFTA Membership w/ 10% discount on all 2010 GAFFTA events (*VERY limited qty) $55 Silver Membership includes: 1 ticket to Powers of 10 1 year GAFFTA Membership w/ 10% discount on all 2010 GAFFTA events $125 Platinum Membership includes: 2 tickets to Powers of 10 1 year GAFFTA Membership w/ 10% discount on all 2010 GAFFTA events and limited edition Aaron Koblin “Flight Patterns” poster $250 Titanium Membership includes: 2 tickets to Powers of 10 1 year GAFFTA Membership w/ 10% discount on all 2010 GAFFTA events limited edition Aaron Koblin “Flight Patterns” poster two tickets to an additional GAFFTAhours event of your choice in 2010 and a bottle of champagne
Thursday, December 31, 2009 at 9:00pm - Friday, January 1, 2010 at 4:00am in PST
Gray Area Foundation for the Arts,55 Taylor Street,San Francisco,California,United States

LAUNCH - BabyMaker: Diapers to Diploma
Mark Zuckerberg was invited
It's finally here. The short version: we've launched our game, BabyMaker: Diapers to Diploma! It's a cute game where you raise children and dress them to your heart's content! The decisions you make as they grow up will ultimately affect their future: college, job, success, family and more! Play now at: www.facebook.com/babymakers === The long version: I'm setting aside all shame and inviting every single one of my Facebook friends to this event b/c my team worked very hard on this. Feel free to unfriend me if you can't remember who I am <3 This game is not for everyone, but we want to find the people who like clicking on cute babies and dressing them up with 1,500+ pieces of clothing and decorating their rooms with 1,500+ pieces of furniture and decoration. We're genuinely excited to share this with you all, and appreciate all the support you've given us to this point. Thank you, we hope you enjoy the game and tell your friends about it too =) Also, for those of you counting, we're giving 10% of all our revenues to child-focused charities, starting with Love146 (www.love146.org) and Room to Read (www.roomtoread.org). We want to do everything right, and that's just one part of it. Cheers and God bless my friends, -Brian
Tuesday, July 26, 2011 at 2:00pm - Monday, August 8, 2011 at 9:30pm in EDT
www.facebook.com/babymakers
